Vue.js uses a reactive data binding system. There are two main types of data binding:

1. One-way data binding: Updates the view from the model (data to UI).
2. Two-way data binding: Synchronizes data between the model 
    and the view (data to UI and UI to data).
Example:


<div id="app">
  <input v-model="message" placeholder="Enter a message">
  <p>{{ message }}</p>
</div>

<script>
  new Vue({
    el: '#app',
    data: {
      message: ''
    }
  });
</script>